<SubSection title="General State of Stress">

The general state of stress at a point is characterized by three independent normal stress components and three independent shear stress components, and is represented by the <strong>stress tensor</strong>. The combination of the state of stress for every point in the domain is called the <strong>stress field</strong>.


<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress Transformation-Figures/General Stress State.png" width="5">  <BlueText>Taken from TAM251 Lecture Notes - L9S2</BlueText></Image>

<DisplayEquation equation="\\begin{bmatrix} \\sigma_{x} & \\tau_{xy} & \\tau_{xz} \\\\ \\tau_{xy} & \\sigma_{y} & \\tau_{yz} \\\\ \\tau_{xz} & \\tau_{yz} & \\sigma_{z} \\end{bmatrix}" />

 <em>Note:</em> stress is a physical quantity and as such, it is independent of the chosen coordinate system.

</SubSection>

