<SubSection title="Mohr's Circle">

<Image src="/mechref/Solid_Mechanics/Stress Transformation-Figures/mohrsCircle.png" width="2"> From ref pages</Image>

 Mohr's circle is a graphical representation of stress transformations. The equations for stress transformations actually describe a circle if we consider the normal stress <InlineEquation equation="\\sigma" /> to be the x-coordinate and the shear stress <InlineEquation equation="\\pi" /> to be the y-coordinate.

 Circle Centroid:

<DisplayEquation equation="C = \\sigma_{avg} = \\frac{\\sigma_x +\\sigma_y}{2} = \\frac{\\sigma_1 +\\sigma_2}{2}\\" />

 Circle Radius:

<DisplayEquation equation="R = \\sqrt{(\\frac{\\sigma_x - \\sigma_y}{2})^2 + \\tau_{xy}^2}\\" />

 We classify two points:

<DisplayEquation equation="\\begin{align} \\rm\\ Point \\ X&: (\\sigma_x, \\tau_{xy}) \\\\ \\rm\\ Point \\ Y&: (\\sigma_y, -\\tau_{xy}) \\end{align}" />
                        
</SubSection>

